messages.message: BTW, I cleaned up the Instabase Infrastructure Requirements doc a bit in terms of minor fixes to grammar/language, as well as adding the bit about Safari not being supported (it’s the second largest browser in terms of market share). If anyone is sending it to customers, you might want to grab a new PDF version (@mmark is the person who made me aware of it, for instance).
I don’t know that many customers are using Instabase from their iDevice (yet). :) Safari is somewhat insignificant when you remove mobile.
StatCounter claims it’s in 3rd place on the desktop, even ahead of IE. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ (though other places rank them slightly differently).
True. There is a big difference between #1 and even #2 though.
I was surprised they were so close when you specify NA on desktop. :D
